{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-single-post-js","path":"/blog/projects/asteroids/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Larqqa's blogfolio"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"659f8181-897a-5d65-a1fd-b92244bd6960","excerpt":"My interpretation of the classic asteroids game. This game was made using vanilla JavaScript. This is one of my earlier projects using JavaScript. I decided toâ€¦","html":"<a href=\"https://github.com/Larqqa/Electron-asteroids\" class=\"icon\">\n  <i class=\"fab fa-github\"></i>\n</a>\n<a href=\"https://those-asteroids.web.app/\" class=\"icon\">\n  <i class=\"fas fa-laptop\"></i>\n</a>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1200px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 49%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"asteroids\"\n        title=\"asteroids\"\n        src=\"/static/f95905765f26852532f162d05a674072/c1b63/asteroids.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/f95905765f26852532f162d05a674072/5a46d/asteroids.png 300w,\n/static/f95905765f26852532f162d05a674072/0a47e/asteroids.png 600w,\n/static/f95905765f26852532f162d05a674072/c1b63/asteroids.png 1200w,\n/static/f95905765f26852532f162d05a674072/d61c2/asteroids.png 1800w,\n/static/f95905765f26852532f162d05a674072/9ce1c/asteroids.png 1886w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p>My interpretation of the classic asteroids game. This game was made using vanilla JavaScript.</p>\n<p>This is one of my earlier projects using JavaScript. I decided to heavily rely on objects in JavaScript, which made handling the game state much easier. The basis for this very simple game engine was the HTML <code class=\"language-text\">canvas</code> element and <code class=\"language-text\">setInterval</code> to control the game loop.</p>\n<p>The most difficulty I had with this project was the positioning and movements of all the game pieces, and the interactions between these pieces. I had to study implementing 2D coordinate systems in Javascript and implementing simple physics-esque calculations for the game. For example the ship uses a drag system for the movement. You apply a force when you want to move the ship, and it slows down with a constant drag every loop.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Asteroids","date":"May 30, 2018","update":null,"description":"Asteroids game made in vanilla JavaScript"}},"morePosts":{"nodes":[{"fields":{"slug":"/blog/ideas/wordpress-gulp-setup/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Gulp & webpack setup for Wordpress development"}},{"fields":{"slug":"/blog/projects/mandelbrot-set-visualizer/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Mandelbrot set visualizer"}},{"fields":{"slug":"/blog/ideas/plotting-the-mandelbrot-set/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Plotting the Mandelbrot set"}},{"fields":{"slug":"/blog/ideas/wordpress-dynamic-ip/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Dynamic Wordpress siteurl"}},{"fields":{"slug":"/blog/projects/advent-of-code/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Advent Of Code 2020"}}]}},"pageContext":{"tags":["Projects","Gamedev","JavaScript"],"slug":"/blog/projects/asteroids/","previous":null,"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/blog/projects/color-picker/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Color Picker","tags":["Projects","Java"],"date":"2019-07-10"}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3000541721","845761813"]}